description: In this remote village where everyone ice skates, you have to prove your skating skills to gain entrance!

puzzles.description: Make Dash automatically turn on white lights, turn on three eye lights, and play the Let's go! #3 sound.
puzzles.introduction: Dash is a little nervous but is ready to skate anyway!

puzzles.description: Edit the first Moving Basics state (the one on the left) to: left wheel 40 cm/s, right wheel 30 cm/s. Then edit the other Moving Basics state: left wheel 30 cm/s, right wheel 40 cm/s.
puzzles.introduction: Making the wheels go forward slowly at different speeds with short pauses in between creates the skating effect. We added some code to help with this step.

puzzles.description: Tap on the new eye ring and turn off some of the lights to give Dash a smile. Link the listener to the eye ring so that Dash smiles after 8.0 s.
puzzles.introduction: The Listener works at the same time as the main code. It waits until a cue causes it to change to a new state.

hints.description: If you use the Wait For cue set to 8.0 s, the Listener will interrupt the main program after 8.0 s, and Dash will smile.

puzzles.description: Create a loop by connecting the two new Moving Basics states with two Wait For cues set to 2.0 s.
puzzles.introduction: Dash is no longer nervous and is ready for some fancy moves!

hints.description: Create a loop out of the two Moving Basics states by linking them together with two Wait For cues set to 2.0 s.
